    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NAMED_EVENT

        public static final TriggerType.Value NAMED_EVENT
        Named Event

        The trigger occurs in response to a specific named event, and no other information about the trigger is specified. Named events are completely pre-coordinated, and the formal semantics of the trigger are not provided.

      • PERIODIC

        public static final TriggerType.Value PERIODIC
        Periodic

        The trigger occurs at a specific time or periodically as described by a timing or schedule. A periodic event cannot have any data elements, but may have a name assigned as a shorthand for the event.

      • DATA_CHANGED

        public static final TriggerType.Value DATA_CHANGED
        Data Changed

        The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is changed in any way, either added, modified, or removed.

      • DATA_ADDED

        public static final TriggerType.Value DATA_ADDED
        Data Added

        The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is added.

      • DATA_MODIFIED

        public static final TriggerType.Value DATA_MODIFIED
        Data Updated

        The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is modified.

      • DATA_REMOVED

        public static final TriggerType.Value DATA_REMOVED
        Data Removed

        The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is removed.

      • DATA_ACCESSED

        public static final TriggerType.Value DATA_ACCESSED
        Data Accessed

        The trigger occurs whenever data of a particular type is accessed.

      • DATA_ACCESS_ENDED

        public static final TriggerType.Value DATA_ACCESS_ENDED
        Data Access Ended

        The trigger occurs whenever access to data of a particular type is completed.
